The paper deals with the problem of finding a maximum matching in a graph given by an input stream, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The problem is formulated in terms of maximizing a monotone submodular function, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and has applications in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG). The algorithms presented in the paper use techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Overall, the paper covers a broad range of topics in computer science, but the focus on data structures and discrete mathematics suggests that cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely categories.
